Program: The Forum
Title: Maps and Mapmaking
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p011qhpc
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 16 Dec 2012
Every map has a story, and every mapmaker approaches their work with some kind of agenda. Carrie Gracie discusses where the urge to make maps comes from and what they mean to us; with American earth scientist Greg Asner, British historian of cartography Jerry Brotton and German-Greek map designer Aris Venetikidis. Illustration by Rosemary Baker. Show less